Metrics.Description: The mass of the walkie-talkie; Must be less than 250 grams, ideal is 100
Metrics.Name: WalkieTalkieMass

Metrics.Description: The length of the walkie-talkie; Must be less than 150 mm, ideal is 80
Metrics.Name: WalkieTalkieLength

Metrics.Description: The width across the face of the walkie-talkie; Must be less than 70 mm, ideal is 40
Metrics.Name: WalkieTalkieWidth

Metrics.Description: The depth of the walkie-talkie; Must be less than 50 mm, ideal is 30
Metrics.Name: WalkieTalkieDepth

Metrics.Description: The range of the walkie-talkie where communication confidence drops below 95%; Must be greater than 2000 m Line of Sight, ideal is 10000 m
Metrics.Name: Range

Metrics.Description: The power consumed by the walkie-talkie while transmitting; must be less than 5 watts
Metrics.Name: AvgPowerTx

Metrics.Description: The power consumed by the walkie-talkie while receiving; must be less than 1 watt
Metrics.Name: AvgPowerRx

Metrics.Description: The power consumed by the walkie-talkie while idle; must be less than 0.5 watt
Metrics.Name: AvgPowerIdle

Metrics.Description: The cost of the parts and materials to manufacture this walkie-talkie
Metrics.Name: MaterialCost

Metrics.Description: The time to assemble one walkie-talkie
Metrics.Name: Labor

Metrics.Description: The ratio of unit price to unit cost; reflects profitability
Metrics.Name: ProfitRatio
